{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"naturalnocasecmpTo(_:)","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot10StringNameC18naturalnocasecmpToys5Int64VSSF","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"naturalnocasecmpTo"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int64V","text":"Int64","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/StringName"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/stringname\/naturalnocasecmpto(_:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"naturalnocasecmpTo"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"to"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int64V","text":"Int64","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When used for sorting, natural order comparison orders sequences of numbers by the combined value of each digit as is often expected, instead of the single digit’s value. A sorted sequence of numbered strings will be ","type":"text"},{"code":"[\"1\", \"2\", \"3\", ...]","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", not "},{"code":"[\"1\", \"10\", \"2\", \"3\", ...]","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With different string lengths, returns ","type":"text"},{"code":"1","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if this string is longer than the ","type":"text"},{"code":"to","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" string, or ","type":"text"},{"code":"-1","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if shorter. Note that the length of empty strings is "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"always","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get a [bool] result from a string comparison, use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"type":"text","text":" operator instead. See also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"naturalcasecmpTo(to:)"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nocasecmpTo(to:)"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"casecmpTo(to:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Performs a ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"case-insensitive","type":"text"}]},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"natural order","type":"text"}]},{"text":" comparison to another string. Returns ","type":"text"},{"code":"-1","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if less than, ","type":"text"},{"code":"1","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if greater than, or "},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if equal. “Less than” or “greater than” are determined by the "},{"text":"Unicode code points","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" of each string, which roughly matches the alphabetical order. Internally, lowercase characters are converted to uppercase for the comparison."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/StringName\/naturalnocasecmpTo(_:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc:/